  "prompt": "How much time is required for the entire selection process of IAS?",
  "response": "The Indian Administrative Service (IAS) selection process, which is conducted by the Union Public Service Commission (UPSC), typically takes about a year to complete. Here is a breakdown of the different stages and their approximate timeframes:\n\n1. **Notification and Application:**\n   - The UPSC releases the notification for the Civil Services Examination (CSE) in February or March.\n   - The application process lasts for about three to four weeks.\n\n2. **Preliminary Examination (Prelims):**\n   - The prelims are usually conducted in May or June, about two to three months after the notification.\n   - Results are typically announced within six to eight weeks after the exam.\n\n3. **Main Examination (Mains):**\n   - The mains are held approximately three to four months after the announcement of the prelims results, usually in September or October.\n   - It takes about two to three months for the results of the mains to be declared.\n\n4. **Interview/Personality Test:**\n   - The interview stage takes place a few months after the mains results, generally starting in January or February of the following year.\n   - The entire interview process can take one to two months to complete.\n\n5. **Final Results:**\n   - The final results, which include the combined scores of the mains and interview, are usually announced in May or June, approximately a year after the initial notification.\n\nOverall, from the release of the notification to the announcement of the final results, the entire IAS selection process spans about 12 to 14 months. However, these timeframes can vary slightly from year to year based on UPSC's scheduling and the number of candidates at each stage.",
